From: retropangui <retropangui@odroidc5>
Date: Sat, 28 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] udev_input: enable xkb_handling for khr_display context

VK_KHR_display (khr_display) context driver is used on KMS/DRM with
Vulkan, but udev_input_init() only enables xkb_handling when the
context ident is "kms" (which is the EGL/DRM context). As a result,
keyboard text input is broken when using the Vulkan renderer on KMS:
input_keyboard_event() is called with character=0 and mod=0, making
text entry in the menu (search, etc.) non-functional.

Fix by also enabling xkb_handling for "khr_display".
---
 input/drivers/udev_input.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/input/drivers/udev_input.c b/input/drivers/udev_input.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/input/drivers/udev_input.c
+++ b/input/drivers/udev_input.c
@@ -4097,7 +4097,8 @@
    /* Force xkb_handling on Lakka */
    udev->xkb_handling = true;
 #else
-   udev->xkb_handling = string_is_equal(ctx_ident.ident, "kms");
+   udev->xkb_handling = string_is_equal(ctx_ident.ident, "kms") ||
+                        string_is_equal(ctx_ident.ident, "khr_display");
 #endif /* HAVE_LAKKA */
 #endif
